Sarhea: why don't you just further define what a personal attack means? Then you can place it in the rules thread and everyone will be able to read it, and then there's just no excuse for breaking it. I have no problem with the other rules, it's just this one that's kinda iffy. Moderators wouldn't have to think about what to do with a particular post, they could just reference it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderating inconsistently<br>since Jun 2002</span><br>  Posts: 1694<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/20/02 3:54:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1591.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enforcement of the rules</span><hr size=1> Speakin for myself, simplest description perhaps is that personal attacks = insults about the player themself -vs- their behaviour in-game.<br>
<br>
If I call someone a thief and a liar who ripped me off in the bazaar, it might be harsh, but it's not a personal attack.<br>
<br>
If I call someone a f***ing asshole jerkwad buttmuncher who probably can't get a date if he tried, that's a personal attack.<br>
<br>
Personal attacks tend to get moderated differently based on the severity of the comments, and the circumstances surrounding the comments (were the comments provoked or just out of the blue, etc).  <br>
<br>
If Rollen said that Coinfist had a stupid looking helmet, and coinfist said that he met Rollen at fanfaire and he had B.O., that might be a personal attack but it's probably not anything severe enough that we'd step in unless Rollen e-mailed us about it or something.<br>
<br>
