<br>
   It's difficult to determine intent at those speeds.  Were they trying to speed?  Is there just a downhill slope in the road?  Were they just listening to some fast paced music and not paying attention?  Is everyone else on the road going a little over the limit also?<br>
<br>
   Policing the boards so strictly that any comment that could be possibly construed as maybe being some kind of personal attack if someone read it one way or another takes far more work than anyone is ever going to put into on a message board.   You'll never know for sure what the intent was when you're policing those little ones, and every time a decision is made it'll get contested by one side or the other.  <br>
<br>
   So, it just becomes a judgement call, and there ya go <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
