And No, equal treatment isn't too much to expect, and I think we do our damnedest, given what we've got to work with.<br>
<br>
Yes, we mods dance a fine line, we know this. And every few months it pisses someone off. go back through the posts, you'll see this is true.<br>
<br>
I will not be changing my mod style, although, as always, I welcome...opinions, and Tzaroth, I understand that you honestly want to know these things, which is why I'm trying my best to answer you*Smile*<br>
<br>
We don't, as a mod team, set out to single anyone out, nor do we play favorites. <br>
<br>
Obviously, we all have posters that we'd rather just not post ever again*smile* But in cases like that, we almost always will ask the other mods...&quot;Is this post outta line or is it just me?&quot; <br>
<br>
We do everything in our power to make sure no one's getting made a scapegoat, even when, sometimes, I think they've asked for it.<br>
<br>
Maybe it would be better, if we were paid by VI or ezboard to spend 8 hours a day reading the boards, and keeping up with everything.<br>
<br>
I'm sure all of us have made mod decisions that, if we were to go back, we wouldn't make a second time.  We're people, and we all try to be impartial, but sometimes our humanity gets the best of us.<br>
<br>
You're asking for a perfect system when it's an impossibility given the environment.<br>
<br>
I'm just explaining to you that we're doing the best we can, really.<br>
<br>
